elements.title: NGC 1700
elements.contents: ... that the galaxy NGC 1700 (pictured) has a rotating hot gas disk glowing in X-rays after merging with another galaxy three billion years ago?

elements.title: Ed Storm
elements.contents: ... that coach Ed Storm, after seeing his American football team losing late in a game, put on a uniform, entered the game, and made the game-winning score?

elements.title: Manon Lescaut
elements.contents: ... that the 1731 novel Manon Lescaut did not become popular in France until after it was banned for immorality?

elements.title: Rashid Israr
elements.contents: ... that it took 12 and a half hours for Rashid Israr to reach his highest score in cricket?

elements.title: His Majesty Bunker Bean
elements.contents: ... that the American play His Majesty Bunker Bean was a national hit that had "been seen by most of the country east of the Mississippi River" before it reached Broadway?

elements.title: Andrew Cushin
elements.contents: ... that singer Andrew Cushin used to play as a goalkeeper in Newcastle Benfield F.C.'s youth team?

elements.title: Helmover torpedo
elements.contents: ... that a model prototype of the Helmover torpedo went out of control while under test and struck a motor launch?

elements.title: Bradley Smalley
elements.contents: ... that Bradley Smalley, the political boss of the Vermont Democratic Party, once received the Republican nomination for alderman?

elements.title: Djabal Club d'Iconi
elements.contents: ... that Comorian football club Djabal Club d'Iconi were deducted two points in the 2023–24 season after a player was found guilty of witchcraft?
